Impyla tries to import Pandas, and when it fails, [it will print](https://github.com/cloudera/impyla/blob/master/impala/util.py#L26-L27) "Failed to import pandas". I'm using Impyla as part of a command line tool, so this message will always pop up when Pandas is not installed, even though I have no need of the `as_pandas()` method, and thus don't want to force users to install Pandas.
If Impyla would make use of Python's logging facilities, I could at least "swallow" that message in my app by also configuring logging. Any ETA [on this](https://github.com/cloudera/impyla/issues/23)? 

Maybe even better would be to do the Pandas import _inside_ the `as_pandas()` method. Like this:
```python
def as_pandas(cursor):
    try:
        import pandas as pd
        names = [metadata[0] for metadata in cursor.description]
        return pd.DataFrame.from_records(cursor.fetchall(), columns=names)
    except ImportError:
        print "Failed to import pandas"
```

Hello there. I experienced a segfault when loading a .ASE file. Apparently, two nodes were referring each other. I avoided the segfault with this simple patch:
```
diff --git a/code/ASELoader.cpp b/code/ASELoader.cpp
index 3a78e06..13bfb5f 100644
--- a/code/ASELoader.cpp
+++ b/code/ASELoader.cpp
@@ -579,7 +579,7 @@ void ASEImporter::AddNodes (const std::vector<BaseNode*>& nodes,
                node->mTransformation = mParentAdjust*snode->mTransform;
 
                // Add sub nodes - prevent stack overflow due to recursive parenting
-           if (node->mName != node->mParent->mName) {
+         if (node->mName != node->mParent->mName && node->mName != node->mParent->mParent->mName) {
                        AddNodes(nodes,node,node->mName.data,snode->mTransform);
                }
```
 but I have no idea whatsoever if this is the proper way to solve the problem. I can submit a pull request if needed. Let me know...

Hi, 

I recently loaded an obj file that was created by Luxion Keyshot. When loading it via assimp, either in the viewer demo app or in my own code the material names are broken. The issue is that the names contain white spaces. 
```
-------------------------------------------------------
# OBJ Material Export by Luxion KeyShot

newmtl Anodized Rough Grey #1
Kd 0 0 0
Ks 0.515023 0.515023 0.515022

newmtl Hard Shiny Plastic White
Kd 1 1 1
Ks 0.992157 0.992157 0.992157

newmtl Hard Rough Plastic Black
Kd 0.0117647 0.0117647 0.0117647
Ks 0.992157 0.992157 0.992157
....
-------------------------------------------------------
```
In this example the parser will only discover two material names "Anodized"and "Hard" instead of "Anodized Rough Grey #1", "Hard Shiny Plastic White", "Hard Rough Plastic Black". 

Following a patch that resolves the issue for me and allows me to import the model correctly.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
```
diff --git a/code/ObjFileMtlImporter.cpp b/code/ObjFileMtlImporter.cpp
index bef8e47..7f6365b 100644
--- a/code/ObjFileMtlImporter.cpp
+++ b/code/ObjFileMtlImporter.cpp
@@ -268,7 +268,14 @@ void ObjFileMtlImporter::createMaterial()
 	if ( numToken == 1 ) {
 		name = AI_DEFAULT_MATERIAL_NAME;
 	} else {
-		name = token[ 1 ];
+        // skip newmtl and all following white spaces
+        std::size_t first_ws_pos = line.find_first_of(" \t");
+        ai_assert(first_ws_pos != std::string::npos);
+        std::size_t first_non_ws_pos = line.find_first_not_of(" \t", first_ws_pos);
+        ai_assert(first_non_ws_pos != std::string::npos);
+        if (first_non_ws_pos != std::string::npos) {
+            name = line.substr(first_non_ws_pos);
+        }
 	}
 
 	std::map<std::string, ObjFile::Material*>::iterator it = m_pModel->m_MaterialMap.find( name );
diff --git a/code/ObjFileParser.cpp b/code/ObjFileParser.cpp
index 9c59828..2ffc417 100644
--- a/code/ObjFileParser.cpp
+++ b/code/ObjFileParser.cpp
@@ -469,7 +469,7 @@ void ObjFileParser::getMaterialDesc()
         return;
 
     char *pStart = &(*m_DataIt);
-    while( m_DataIt != m_DataItEnd && !IsSpaceOrNewLine( *m_DataIt ) ) {
+    while (m_DataIt != m_DataItEnd && !IsLineEnd(*m_DataIt)) {
         ++m_DataIt;
     }
 ```

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

